00:04:04.249 --> 00:04:08.580
- Hmm, no, it should still
take around 10 minutes.

00:04:08.580 --> 00:04:12.713
Ultimately you're doing
around four sets per workout.

00:04:15.180 --> 00:04:17.060
Remember just stick to the one.

00:04:17.060 --> 00:04:19.790
Some people really like
doing two sets per workout

00:04:20.660 --> 00:04:23.360
for the exercise, I still do one.

00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:25.690
I did experiment with two for a little bit

00:04:25.690 --> 00:04:26.930
but I went back to one.

00:04:26.930 --> 00:04:28.920
You just go to a deeper
level of exhaustion.

00:04:28.920 --> 00:04:32.150
Also when you know you've
gotta get the job done

00:04:32.150 --> 00:04:35.870
with one set, you're gonna
behave a little differently.

00:04:35.870 --> 00:04:38.300
You're going to go to absolute fatigue

00:04:38.300 --> 00:04:40.550
in all ranges of motion simultaneously,

00:04:40.550 --> 00:04:42.833
something you cannot do with a weight.

00:04:43.690 --> 00:04:47.360
Therefore, the depth of exhaustion.

00:04:47.360 --> 00:04:50.210
You're trying to show the
central nervous system

00:04:50.210 --> 00:04:52.020
a deficit of tissue.

00:04:52.020 --> 00:04:55.340
Like, we don't have enough
muscle here, we need more.

00:04:55.340 --> 00:04:58.520
So the more intense the stimulus

00:04:58.520 --> 00:05:00.270
in the shorter period of time,

00:05:00.270 --> 00:05:02.380
not the longer period, the
shorter period of time,

00:05:02.380 --> 00:05:03.520
shows the central nervous system

00:05:03.520 --> 00:05:06.970
that clearly more power is needed here.

00:05:06.970 --> 00:05:10.800
And that is the clearer signal.

00:05:10.800 --> 00:05:14.610
So advanced programming
involves some holds

00:05:14.610 --> 00:05:18.150
to really make sure
you're going to fatigue

00:05:18.150 --> 00:05:19.980
at whatever peak you're at.

00:05:19.980 --> 00:05:22.760
So like in a bicep curl here, I'm holding,

00:05:22.760 --> 00:05:23.990
and then I can't hold there anymore

00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:26.450
and then I have a shorter
rep and I'm holding there,

00:05:26.450 --> 00:05:27.730
I do a few of those.

00:05:27.730 --> 00:05:30.180
And then, you know, the last rep is a very

00:05:30.180 --> 00:05:33.610
very low range repetition
and a weaker range of motion

00:05:33.610 --> 00:05:35.260
and then going to fatigue there.

00:05:35.260 --> 00:05:39.290
So making sure you're
really just asking yourself,

00:05:39.290 --> 00:05:41.320
am I really going to fatigue here?

00:05:41.320 --> 00:05:45.390
And those holds will
tell you, yeah you are.

00:05:45.390 --> 00:05:49.270
So very, very clear signals.

